    • findSlotDates

      public static List<LocalDate> findSlotDates(List<Appointment> availableSlots)
      This method takes a list of appointment slots and returns a sorted list of dates from the earliest to the latest date available. The list includes every consecutive date between the start and end date found in the appointment slots.
      Parameters:
      availableSlots - the list of appointments from which to extract and sort dates
      Returns:
      a list of LocalDate objects representing each consecutive date between the earliest and latest dates found in the slots

    • splitAppointmentDates

      public static List<List<Appointment>> splitAppointmentDates(List<Appointment> availableSlots, List<LocalDate> dates)
      This method divides a list of appointments into sublists, each containing all appointments for a particular date. It uses a sorted list of dates to organize appointments into these date-specific lists.
      Parameters:
      availableSlots - the complete list of appointments to be categorized by date
      dates - a sorted list of dates for which appointments need to be organized
      Returns:
      a list of lists, where each sublist contains all appointments for a specific date
